HC 10—RC 2514/DI hf

January 27, 2026
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
HOUSE CONCURRENT
RESOLUTION No. 10
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION urging the Indiana
2 Department of Transportation to rename that portion of State
3 Highway 558 between U.S. Highway 231 and the Northwest
4 Gate of Naval Support Activity Crane the "Commodore Crane
5 Highway".
6 Whereas, In 1941, the United States Congress enacted the
7 first National Defense Appropriation Act, authorizing funding
8 for new inland ammunition production facilities to support the
9 national defense;
10 Whereas, Pursuant to that Act, the Naval Ammunition Depot,
11 Burns City, Indiana, was established as an inland ammunition
12 production facility due to its remote location, suitable terrain,
13 and access to critical transportation, utilities, and
14 infrastructure;
15 Whereas, In May 1943, the depot was renamed the Naval
16 Ammunition Depot, Crane, in honor of Commodore William
17 Montgomery Crane, the United States Navy's first Chief of the
18 Bureau of Ordnance, for whom the installation continues to be
19 named;
20 Whereas, Following World War II, Crane evolved into a
21 multi-mission defense installation supporting advanced
22 engineering, electronics, logistics, ammunition, and weapons
23 systems critical to national security;
24 Whereas, Today, Naval Support Activity Crane, the
25 third-largest naval installation in the world, is home to multiple
HC 10—RC 2514/DI hf

2
1 major military commands, including the Naval Surface Warfare
2 Center, Crane Division, and the Crane Army Ammunition
3 Activity, which together, with other tenant commands, are
4 known collectively as Team Crane;
5 Whereas, Team Crane provides global support to the United
6 States Navy, Army, and joint war-fighting missions and
7 represents one of Indiana's most significant strategic,
8 economic, and national security assets;
9 Whereas, Local and state leaders recognize the importance of
10 visibly demonstrating Indiana's support for Naval Support
11 Activity Crane and all of its tenant commands;
12 Whereas, Renaming the portion of State Highway 558
13 between U.S. Highway 231 and the Northwest Gate of Naval
14 Support Activity Crane as the "Commodore Crane Highway"
15 honors the individual for whom the installation is named,
16 improves identification and wayfinding, and increases public
17 awareness of the installation and its mission; and
18 Whereas, Such recognition underscores Indiana's
19 commitment to supporting Naval Support Activity Crane, its
20 workforce, and its tenant command. It strengthens the
21 demonstration of local and state support critical to the
22 installation's continued success and future mission
23 responsibilities: Therefore,
24 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives
25 of the General Assembly of the State of Indiana,
26 the Senate concurring:
27 SECTION 1. That the Indiana General Assembly urges the
28 Indiana Department of Transportation to rename that portion of
29 State Highway 558 between U.S. Highway 231 and the
30 Northwest Gate of Naval Support Activity Crane the
31 "Commodore Crane Highway".
32 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
33 Representatives shall transmit copies of this resolution to the
34 Commissioner of the Indiana Department of Transportation.
HC 10—RC 2514/DI hf

3
COMMITTEE REPORT
Mr. Speaker: Your Committee on Roads and Transportation, to
which was referred House Concurrent Resolution 10, has had the same
under consideration and begs leave to report the same back to the
House with the recommendation that said resolution do pass.
(Reference is to HC 10 as printed January 13, 2026.)
PRESSEL
Committee Vote: Yeas 11, Nays 0
